      <hr />
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <div class="definition">
         <div>
            <p>Medium of performance term used as a heading in an established term record or a 
               traced or an untraced reference record. The term may consist of more than one word. 
            </p>
         </div>
         <div>
            <p>In an established term record, field 162 contains the established form of a medium
               of performance term. In records for references, this field contains an unestablished
               form of a medium of performance term.
            </p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <div class="guidelines">
         <div>
            <p>Guidelines for applying the content designators defined for field 162 and input
               conventions are given in the 
               <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/adx62.html">X62 Medium of Performance Terms-General Information</a></em>
               section.
            </p>
         </div>
